<refsect1 id="gst-plugins-good-plugins-v4l2src.description" role="desc">
<title role="desc.title">Description</title>
<para>v4l2src can be used to capture video from v4l2 devices, like webcams and tv
cards.</para>
<refsect2>
<title>Example launch lines</title>
<informalexample><programlisting><![CDATA[
gst-launch-1.0 v4l2src ! xvimagesink
]]></programlisting></informalexample> This pipeline shows the video captured from /dev/video0 tv card and for
webcams.
<informalexample><programlisting><![CDATA[
gst-launch-1.0 v4l2src ! jpegdec ! xvimagesink
]]></programlisting></informalexample> This pipeline shows the video captured from a webcam that delivers jpeg
images.
</refsect2>

