<refsect2 id="GstV4l2Src-prepare-format" role="signal"><title>The <literal>“prepare-format”</literal> signal</title>
<indexterm role="0.10.32" zone="GstV4l2Src-prepare-format"><primary>GstV4l2Src::prepare-format</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting language="C"><link linkend="void"><returnvalue>void</returnvalue></link>
user_function (<link linkend="GstV4l2Src"><type>GstV4l2Src</type></link> *v4l2src,
               <link linkend="gint"><type>gint</type></link>        fd,
               <link linkend="GstCaps"><type>GstCaps</type></link>    *caps,
               <link linkend="gpointer"><type>gpointer</type></link>    user_data)</programlisting>
<para>This signal gets emitted before calling the v4l2 VIDIOC_S_FMT ioctl
(set format). This allows for any custom configuration of the device to
happen prior to the format being set.
This is mostly useful for UVC H264 encoding cameras which need the H264
Probe &amp; Commit to happen prior to the normal Probe &amp; Commit.</para>
